NOTES:

Requires 68020+(no FPU), OS 3.x, 1+ MiB of free memory, working MMU strongly
recommended!

To see what is on the image mount it using some third party proggy or transfer
it to real floppy with some unadf tool.

Before you boot, open the window of 'CPTInstall_3.x' on your Workbench, click
once on 'CTRL', go Information... and set the desired screenmode. After its
loaded, press Left Amiga + M to read the infos dumped to the BOOTShell.

CompactInstall makes use of FRAP(NSD64/TD64) if you got working mmu and/or
NSDPatch(NSD64 only) with minimal configuration file.

PLEASE NOTE, DONT USE NSDPatch ALONE TO FORMAT PARTITIONS BEYOND 7.8 GiB -
THIS IS SUICIDE - YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED!

CompactInstall includes 'novahdguide.txt' and 'SmartFileSystem'!

